a luau or casino night.

346
00:25:02,733 --> 00:25:05,566
It'll be just like senior year
except funnier.

347
00:25:07,504 --> 00:25:10,064
Time to go.
I have to go to class...

348
00:25:10,107 --> 00:25:11,836
but meet me after
on the benches.

349
00:25:11,875 --> 00:25:13,206
All right, bye!

350
00:25:30,294 --> 00:25:34,128
A legal education
means you will learn...

351
00:25:34,164 --> 00:25:36,826
to speak in a new language.

352
00:25:38,035 --> 00:25:39,935
You will be taught
to achieve insight...

353
00:25:39,970 --> 00:25:43,167
into the world around you...

354
00:25:43,206 --> 00:25:47,438
and to sharply question
what you know.

355
00:25:49,246 --> 00:25:52,147
The seat you have picked
will be yours...

356
00:25:52,182 --> 00:25:56,209
for the next nine months
of your life.

357
00:25:56,253 --> 00:25:58,016
And those of you
in the front row...

358
00:25:59,957 --> 00:26:01,219
beware.

359
00:26:03,827 --> 00:26:07,695
"The law is reason
free from passion."

360
00:26:07,731 --> 00:26:11,292
Does anyone know
who spoke those immortal words?

361
00:26:13,770 --> 00:26:16,739
- Yes?
- Aristotle.

362
00:26:22,145 --> 00:26:23,612
Are you sure?

363
00:26:24,948 --> 00:26:28,543
Would you be willing
to stake your life on it?

364
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:31,285
I think so.

365
00:26:34,658 --> 00:26:38,116
What about his life?

366
00:26:42,666 --> 00:26:43,792
I don't know.

367
00:26:43,834 --> 00:26:49,067
Well, I recommend
knowing before speaking.

368
00:26:49,106 --> 00:26:54,134
The law leaves much room
for interpretation...

369
00:26:54,177 --> 00:26:58,113
but very little for self-doubt.

370
00:26:58,148 --> 00:27:00,116
And you were right.

371
00:27:01,784 --> 00:27:03,911
It was Aristotle.

372
00:27:03,953 --> 00:27:05,215
Good job.

373
00:27:06,355 --> 00:27:10,052
Now, I assume all of you
have read pages 1-48...

374
00:27:10,092 --> 00:27:13,323
and are now well-versed
in subject matter jurisdiction.

375
00:27:13,362 --> 00:27:17,196
Who can tell us about
Gordon vs. Steele?

376
00:27:17,233 --> 00:27:20,225
Let's call on someone
from the hot zone.

377
00:27:37,353 --> 00:27:39,287
Elle Woods?

378
00:27:43,025 --> 00:27:47,223
Actually, I wasn't aware
that we had an assignment.

379
00:27:59,508 --> 00:28:01,066
Vivian Kensington.

380
00:28:01,110 --> 00:28:05,103
Do you think it's acceptable
that Ms. Woods is not prepared?

381
00:28:10,653 --> 00:28:11,915
I don't.

382
00:28:11,954 --> 00:28:15,890
Would you support my decision
to ask her to leave class...

383
00:28:15,925 --> 00:28:19,361
and to return
only when she is prepared?

384
00:28:19,395 --> 00:28:21,056
Absolutely.

385
00:28:40,149 --> 00:28:41,514
Now, Ms. Kensington...

386
00:28:41,550 --> 00:28:44,883
did diversity jurisdiction
exist in this case?

387
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:48,378
No, it did not.

388
00:28:48,424 --> 00:28:51,518
Good. How about in the case
of Owens vs. McCullogh?

389
00:28:51,560 --> 00:28:54,051
I can't believe that girl.

390
00:28:54,096 --> 00:28:56,121
So stupid!

391
00:29:03,539 --> 00:29:05,097
Who does she think she is?

392
00:29:05,140 --> 00:29:07,631
Excuse me. Are you OK?

393
00:29:10,446 --> 00:29:13,779
Do they put you on the spot
like that all the time?

394
00:29:13,816 --> 00:29:14,942
The professors?

395
00:29:14,984 --> 00:29:18,511
They tend to do that.
Socratic method.

396
00:29:18,554 --> 00:29:22,650
If you don't know the answers,
they just kick you out?

397
00:29:22,691 --> 00:29:24,158
You have Stromwell, huh?

398
00:29:24,193 --> 00:29:26,559
Yes!
Did she do that to you, too?

399
00:29:26,595 --> 00:29:28,654
No.
But she did make me cry once.

400
00:29:28,697 --> 00:29:31,222
Not in class. I waited
till I got back to my room...

401
00:29:31,267 --> 00:29:33,394
but she'll kick you
right in the ball...

402
00:29:33,435 --> 00:29:34,868
Or wherever, you know.

403
00:29:34,903 --> 00:29:37,428
She's really tough.

404
00:29:37,473 --> 00:29:39,441
Great.

405
00:29:39,475 --> 00:29:41,841
Don’t worry, it gets better.
Who else do you have?

406
00:29:41,877 --> 00:29:46,974
I have Callahan, Royalton,
and Levinthal.

407
00:29:47,016 --> 00:29:49,314
Let's see, speak up
in Callahan's class.

408
00:29:49,351 --> 00:29:51,911
He really likes people
that are opinionated.

409
00:29:51,954 --> 00:29:54,616
And in Royalton's class...

410
00:29:54,657 --> 00:29:57,251
try to get a seat in the back.

411
00:29:57,293 --> 00:30:00,490
He spits when he talks
about products liability.

412
00:30:00,529 --> 00:30:04,590
And for Levinthal, make sure
you read the footnotes.

413
00:30:04,633 --> 00:30:07,329
That's where he gets
a lot of his exam questions.

414
00:30:07,369 --> 00:30:09,132
Right.

415
00:30:10,706 --> 00:30:13,937
Wow.
I'm really glad I met you.

416
00:30:17,513 --> 00:30:18,673
Are you a third year?

417
00:30:18,714 --> 00:30:20,147
- Well...
- Hey, Elle.

418
00:30:21,317 --> 00:30:24,047
Hi!
Thanks for all your help.

419
00:30:24,086 --> 00:30:25,246
Good luck.

420
00:30:30,993 --> 00:30:32,961
So...

421
00:30:32,995 --> 00:30:34,826
how was your first class?

422
00:30:34,863 --> 00:30:36,990
It was good, except for
this horrible preppy girl...

423
00:30:37,032 --> 00:30:38,897
who made me look bad
in front of the professor.

424
00:30:38,934 --> 00:30:40,629
But no biggie.

425
00:30:40,669 --> 00:30:43,160
You're here now.
So, how was your summer?

426
00:30:43,205 --> 00:30:45,230
Good. It was good.

427
00:30:45,274 --> 00:30:47,674
Did you do anything exciting?

428
00:30:51,080 --> 00:30:54,709
Have you met Vivian?

429
00:30:54,750 --> 00:30:57,913
Hi. Vivian Kensington.

430
00:30:59,788 --> 00:31:01,153
Do you know her?

431
00:31:01,190 --> 00:31:04,648
- She's...
- I'm his fiancée.

432
00:31:12,034 --> 00:31:15,026
I'm sorry.
I just hallucinated. What?

433
00:31:16,438 --> 00:31:20,101
She was my girlfriend
in prep school.

434
00:31:20,142 --> 00:31:22,667
And, well, we got back together
this summer...

435
00:31:22,711 --> 00:31:25,578
at my grandmother's
birthday party.

436
00:31:25,614 --> 00:31:27,707
Warner told me all about you.

437
00:31:27,750 --> 00:31:30,913
You're famous at our club.

438
00:31:30,953 --> 00:31:34,047
But he didn't tell me
you'd be here.

439
00:31:34,089 --> 00:31:37,115
Pooh bear,
I didn't know she would be here.

440
00:31:40,262 --> 00:31:41,923
Excuse me.

441
00:31:58,514 --> 00:32:00,209
Oh, thank God!

442
00:32:17,099 --> 00:32:19,624
Are you free?
It's an emergency.

443
00:32:19,668 --> 00:32:21,295
Bad day?

444
00:32:21,336 --> 00:32:24,464
You can't even imagine.

445
00:32:27,176 --> 00:32:28,302
Spill.

446
00:32:28,343 --> 00:32:32,211
I worked so hard
to get into law school.

447
00:32:32,247 --> 00:32:34,477
I blew off Greek week
to study for the LSATs.

448
00:32:34,516 --> 00:32:37,246
I even hired a Coppola
to direct my admissions video.

449
00:32:37,286 --> 00:32:39,186
All to get
my boyfriend Warner back.

450
00:32:39,221 --> 00:32:42,019
