1284
01:22:01,476 --> 01:22:04,707
We came to see your trial!

1285
01:22:04,746 --> 01:22:08,341
Look how cute.
There's a judge and everything.

1286
01:22:08,383 --> 01:22:11,648
- And jury people.
- Vote for Elle!

1287
01:22:11,686 --> 01:22:13,153
Ladies, take a seat.

1288
01:22:13,188 --> 01:22:15,019
Go, girl.

1289
01:22:20,195 --> 01:22:21,890
Do you swear to tell
the truth, the whole truth...

1290
01:22:21,930 --> 01:22:23,795
and nothing but the truth,
so help you God?

1291
01:22:23,832 --> 01:22:25,424
- I do.
- Be seated.

1292
01:22:27,035 --> 01:22:30,027
Ms. Woods, you may begin
your questioning.

1293
01:22:34,909 --> 01:22:36,843
First of all
I would like to point out...

1294
01:22:36,878 --> 01:22:39,870
that not only is there
no proof in this case...

1295
01:22:39,914 --> 01:22:43,941
but there is a complete
lack of mens rea...

1296
01:22:43,985 --> 01:22:47,819
which by definition tells us
there can be no crime...

1297
01:22:47,856 --> 01:22:50,916
without a vicious will.

1298
01:22:50,959 --> 01:22:53,860
I am aware of the meaning
of mens rea.

1299
01:22:53,895 --> 01:22:55,362
What I'm unaware of...

1300
01:22:55,396 --> 01:22:57,864
is why you're giving me
a vocabulary lesson...

1301
01:22:57,899 --> 01:23:00,035
when you should be
questioning your witness.

1302
01:23:01,870 --> 01:23:03,497
Yes, Your Honor.

1303
01:23:06,841 --> 01:23:08,399
Miss Windham...

1304
01:23:08,443 --> 01:23:11,378
when you arrived
back at the house...

1305
01:23:11,413 --> 01:23:13,904
was your father there?

1306
01:23:13,948 --> 01:23:16,576
Not that I saw,
but like I said...

1307
01:23:16,618 --> 01:23:19,485
I went straight upstairs
to take a shower.

1308
01:23:19,521 --> 01:23:24,720
And when you came downstairs,
what happened?

1309
01:23:24,759 --> 01:23:28,354
I saw Brooke
standing over his body...

1310
01:23:28,396 --> 01:23:30,990
drenched in his blood.

1311
01:23:36,137 --> 01:23:39,265
But Mrs. Windham
didn't have a gun?

1312
01:23:39,307 --> 01:23:41,332
No. She'd stashed it
by then.

1313
01:23:41,376 --> 01:23:43,276
Move to strike that
from the record, Your Honor.

1314
01:23:43,311 --> 01:23:45,279
- It's speculation.
- So stricken.

1315
01:23:47,749 --> 01:23:49,080
Go ahead.

1316
01:23:54,022 --> 01:23:57,355
Miss Windham,
did you hear a shot fired?

1317
01:23:57,392 --> 01:23:59,792
No. I was in the shower.

1318
01:24:02,430 --> 01:24:06,298
So, sometime
in the 20 minutes...

1319
01:24:06,334 --> 01:24:09,929
that you were in the shower,
your father was shot.

1320
01:24:09,971 --> 01:24:11,632
I guess.

1321
01:24:11,673 --> 01:24:15,769
Your father was shot
while you were in the shower...

1322
01:24:15,810 --> 01:24:20,338
but you didn't hear
the shot because...

1323
01:24:23,318 --> 01:24:25,377
because you were in the shower?

1324
01:24:27,489 --> 01:24:30,458
I was washing my hair.

1325
01:24:33,461 --> 01:24:34,951
Where is she going with this?

1326
01:24:34,996 --> 01:24:37,590
Have a little faith, Gerard.

1327
01:24:45,306 --> 01:24:47,171
Miss Windham...

1328
01:24:47,208 --> 01:24:49,472
what had you done
earlier that day?

1329
01:24:49,511 --> 01:24:52,105
I got up...

1330
01:24:52,147 --> 01:24:54,445
got a latte,
went to the gym...

1331
01:24:54,482 --> 01:24:56,677
got a perm, and came home.

1332
01:24:58,019 --> 01:25:00,817
Where you got in the shower?

1333
01:25:00,855 --> 01:25:03,619
I believe the witness
has made it clear...

1334
01:25:03,658 --> 01:25:06,855
that she was in the shower.

1335
01:25:11,633 --> 01:25:13,225
Yes, Your Honor.

1336
01:25:13,268 --> 01:25:17,364
Miss Windham, had you
ever gotten a perm before?

1337
01:25:18,673 --> 01:25:20,766
How many would you say?

1338
01:25:20,808 --> 01:25:24,175
Two a year since I was 12.

1339
01:25:24,212 --> 01:25:26,840
You do the math.

1340
01:25:26,881 --> 01:25:30,442
A girl in my sorority,
Tracy Marcinko, got a perm once.

1341
01:25:30,485 --> 01:25:32,282
We all tried
to talk her out of it.

1342
01:25:32,320 --> 01:25:33,651
Curls weren't
a good look for her.

1343
01:25:33,688 --> 01:25:35,952
She didn't have
your bone structure.

1344
01:25:37,025 --> 01:25:39,493
But, thankfully,
that same day...

1345
01:25:39,527 --> 01:25:41,722
she entered the Beta Delta Pi
wet t-shirt contest...

1346
01:25:41,763 --> 01:25:43,993
where she was completely
hosed down from head to toe.

1347
01:25:44,032 --> 01:25:46,865
Objection!
Why is this relevant?

1348
01:25:46,901 --> 01:25:48,698
I have a point, I promise.

1349
01:25:48,736 --> 01:25:50,033
Then make it.

1350
01:25:50,071 --> 01:25:52,505
Yes, ma'am.

1351
01:25:52,540 --> 01:25:55,873
Chutney, why were
Tracy Marcinko's curls ruined...

1352
01:25:55,910 --> 01:25:58,640
when she got hosed down?

1353
01:25:58,680 --> 01:26:00,079
Because they got wet?

1354
01:26:00,114 --> 01:26:02,446
Exactly. Isn't it
the first cardinal rule...

1355
01:26:02,483 --> 01:26:04,610
of perm maintenance that you're
forbidden to wet your hair...

1356
01:26:04,652 --> 01:26:06,620
for at least 24 hours
after getting a perm...

1357
01:26:06,654 --> 01:26:09,350
at the risk of deactivating
the ammonium thioglycolate?

1358
01:26:12,393 --> 01:26:14,827
And wouldn't somebody
who's had, say,30 perms...

1359
01:26:14,862 --> 01:26:17,092
in their life
be well aware of this rule?

1360
01:26:17,131 --> 01:26:20,032
And if in fact
you weren’t washing your hair...

1361
01:26:20,068 --> 01:26:22,593
as I suspect, because
your curls are still intact...

1362
01:26:22,637 --> 01:26:24,036
wouldn't you have heard
the gunshot?

1363
01:26:24,072 --> 01:26:26,131
And if in fact
you had heard the gunshot...

1364
01:26:26,174 --> 01:26:28,665
Brooke Windham wouldn't have
had time to hide the gun...

1365
01:26:28,710 --> 01:26:30,234
before you got downstairs...

1366
01:26:30,278 --> 01:26:32,269
which would mean you would
have had to have found...

1367
01:26:32,313 --> 01:26:33,780
Mrs. Windham
with a gun in her hand...

1368
01:26:33,815 --> 01:26:36,545
to make your story plausible.
Isn't that right?

1369
01:26:36,584 --> 01:26:38,916
She's my age!
Did she tell you that?

1370
01:26:38,953 --> 01:26:41,547
How would you feel if your
father married someone your age?

1371
01:26:41,589 --> 01:26:44,353
You, however,
had time to hide the gun...

1372
01:26:44,392 --> 01:26:45,518
after you shot your father.

1373
01:26:45,560 --> 01:26:46,857
I didn't mean to shoot him.

1374
01:26:46,894 --> 01:26:49,226
I thought it was you
walking through the door!

1375
01:26:52,133 --> 01:26:54,533
Order! Order!

1376
01:26:54,569 --> 01:26:56,662
Order!

1377
01:26:56,704 --> 01:26:58,569
Oh, my God.

1378
01:26:58,606 --> 01:26:59,868
Oh, my God.

1379
01:26:59,907 --> 01:27:01,738
Oh, my God.

1380
01:27:03,311 --> 01:27:05,802
Bailiff,
take the witness into custody...

1381
01:27:05,847 --> 01:27:09,214
where she will be charged for
the murder of Heyworth Windham.

1382
01:27:09,250 --> 01:27:12,413
In the matter of
The State vs. Brooke Windham...

1383
01:27:12,453 --> 01:27:14,250
this case is dismissed.

1384
01:27:14,289 --> 01:27:16,484
Mrs. Windham,
you are free to go.

1385
01:27:27,769 --> 01:27:29,803
Thank you!

1386
01:27:33,840 --> 01:27:35,899
Elle, how did you know
Chutney was lying?

1387
01:27:35,942 --> 01:27:37,534
Because she's brilliant,
of course.

1388
01:27:37,577 --> 01:27:39,602
The rules of hair care
are simple and finite.

1389
01:27:39,646 --> 01:27:41,409
Any Cosmo Girl
would have known.

1390
01:27:47,187 --> 01:27:48,654
What?

1391
01:27:48,688 --> 01:27:50,315
I just wanted to say...

1392
01:27:50,356 --> 01:27:52,756
that you were
so brilliant in there.

1393
01:27:52,792 --> 01:27:56,523
And that I was wrong.

1394
01:27:56,563 --> 01:28:01,057
And you are the girl for me.

1395
01:28:01,100 --> 01:28:03,762
Really?

1396
01:28:03,803 --> 01:28:07,933
Pooh bear... I love you.

1397
01:28:10,510 --> 01:28:13,775
I've waited so long
to hear you say that.

1398
01:28:15,081 --> 01:28:18,710
But if I'm gonna be a partner at
a law firm by the time I'm 30...

1399
01:28:18,751 --> 01:28:21,379
I need a boyfriend who's not
such a complete bonehead.

1400
01:28:25,992 --> 01:28:27,926
Thank you, boys.

1401
01:28:34,300 --> 01:28:35,631
Ladies and gentlemen...

1402
01:28:35,869 --> 01:28:39,498
I present the graduates
of Harvard Law School...

1403
01:28:39,539 --> 01:28:42,736
Class of 2004.

1404
01:28:44,577 --> 01:28:48,013
I am personally
very honored to introduce...

1405
01:28:48,047 --> 01:28:50,709
this year's
class-elected speaker.

1406
01:28:50,750 --> 01:28:54,379
After getting off
to a quite interesting start...

1407
01:28:54,420 --> 01:28:55,648
here at Harvard...

1408
01:28:55,688 --> 01:28:59,454
she graduates today
with an invitation to join...

1409
01:28:59,492 --> 01:29:02,757
one of Boston's
most prestigious law firms.

1410
01:29:02,795 --> 01:29:07,528
I'm sure we are going to see
great things from her.

1411
01:29:07,567 --> 01:29:11,560
Ladies and gentlemen,
Elle Woods.

1412
01:29:32,759 --> 01:29:34,920
On our very first day
at Harvard...

1413
01:29:34,961 --> 01:29:38,727
a very wise professor
quoted Aristotle.

1414
01:29:38,765 --> 01:29:42,292
"The law is reason
free from passion."

1415
01:29:42,335 --> 01:29:45,771
Well, no offense
to Aristotle...

1416
01:29:45,805 --> 01:29:47,568
but in my three years
at Harvard...

1417
01:29:47,607 --> 01:29:50,974
I have come to find that passion
is a key ingredient...

1418
01:29:51,010 --> 01:29:55,572
to the study and practice
of law and of life.

1419
01:29:55,615 --> 01:29:58,846
It is with passion,
courage of conviction...

1420
01:29:58,885 --> 01:30:00,876
and strong sense of self...

1421
01:30:00,920 --> 01:30:03,480
that we take our next steps
into the world...

1422
01:30:03,523 --> 01:30:05,423
remembering
that first impressions...

1423
01:30:05,458 --> 01:30:07,722
are not always correct...

1424
01:30:07,760 --> 01:30:11,196
you must always have faith
in people...

1425
01:30:11,230 --> 01:30:14,097
and most importantly...

1426
01:30:16,402 --> 01:30:19,667
you must always have faith
in yourself.

1427
01:30:21,174 --> 01:30:24,405
Congratulations, Class of 2004.

1428
01:30:24,444 --> 01:30:26,435
We did it!

